This paper deals with the randomized decision tree complexity of a specific function, which is a topic in computational complexity theory. Therefore, cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is the most likely sub-category. The function being studied involves recursive operations, which suggests that cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also involves analysis of algorithms and probability theory, which could place it in cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.LG (Machine Learning).
